TYPE: Test,
TARGET: interconnection between Control Module 3 output and Control Module 4 input,
DESCRIPTION: With the battery installed and all switches ON, disconnect the connector between Control Module 3 and Control Module 4. Measure continuity of each conductor in the cable/connector pair (from CM3 output pin to CM4 input pin) and also measure voltage on the CM3 side outputs relative to battery negative while the connector is open. Confirm whether +12 V appears on the CM3 side but fails to reach the CM4 side, indicating an open or miswired conductor in this link.,
RESULT: Continuity between Control Output Cable (+) 3 and Control Input Cable (+) 4, and between Control Output Cable (−) 3 and Control Input Cable (−) 4, measures as short (~0.10 Ω) in both cases. All measured voltages (CM3 outputs and CM4 inputs, both + and −) are 0.0 V relative to battery negative with the connector open.
